ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.312                Enzyme
NAME        2-hydroxy-4-carboxymuconate semialdehyde hemiacetal dehydrogenase;
            2-hydroxy-4-carboxymuconate 6-semialdehyde dehydrogenase;
            4-carboxy-2-hydroxy-cis,cis-muconate-6-semialdehyde:NADP+ oxidoreductase;
            alpha-hydroxy-gamma-carboxymuconic epsilon-semialdehyde dehydrogenase;
            4-carboxy-2-hydroxymuconate-6-semialdehyde dehydrogenase;
            LigC;
            ProD
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     4-carboxy-2-hydroxymuconate semialdehyde hemiacetal:NADP+ 2-oxidoreductase
REACTION    4-carboxy-2-hydroxymuconate semialdehyde hemiacetal + NADP+ = 2-oxo-2H-pyran-4,6-dicarboxylate + NADPH + H+ [RN:R04279]
ALL_REAC    R04279;
            (other) R04278 R04418 R04419
SUBSTRATE   4-carboxy-2-hydroxymuconate semialdehyde hemiacetal;
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     2-oxo-2H-pyran-4,6-dicarboxylate;
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme does not act on unsubstituted aliphatic or aromatic aldehydes or glucose; NAD+ can replace NADP+, but with lower affinity. The enzyme was initially believed to act on 4-carboxy-2-hydroxy-cis,cis-muconate 6-semialdehyde and produce 4-carboxy-2-hydroxy-cis,cis-muconate [1]. However, later studies showed that the substrate is the hemiacetal form [3], and the product is 2-oxo-2H-pyran-4,6-dicarboxylate [2,4].
HISTORY     EC 1.1.1.312 created 1978 as EC 1.2.1.45, transferred 2011 to EC 1.1.1.312
